Interface Map<K,V>

  • Type Parameters:
    K - the type of keys maintained by this map
    V - the type of mapped values
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    LinkedDictionary

    public interface Map<K,V>
    Defines the Map abstract data type. An object that maps keys to values. For this project, a map can contain duplicate keys, in which cases the methods get, put, and remove refer to the leftmost (last) association for the given key.
